$3.00 an ounce. Sound impossible? Well, Elgin Resources is on the verge =
of
doing just that.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'text-align:justify;text-autospace:none'><span
style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;color:black'>Allow me to explain. Elgin =
Resources is a
Canadian-based exploration and development company focused on amassing a =
large,
pre-production platinum position in South Africa. In pursuing this =
strategy,
the company is taking advantage of that country&#146;s wholesale =
divestiture of
exploration assets.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'text-align:justify;text-autospace:none'><span
style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;color:black'>As regular readers will remember, =
the
South African government precipitated this fire sale by issuing a =
&#147;use it or
lose it&#148; edict to the majors. The policy is part of larger effort =
to transfer a
portion of the nation&#146;s mineral wealth to its =
historically-disadvantaged black
majority.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'text-align:justify;text-autospace:none'><span
style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;color:black'>By definition, &#147;use it or =
lose it&#148; puts a
premium on producing assets. As a result, the country&#146;s majors =
&#151; driven to cut
costs by the current strong rand regime &#151; have chosen to shed large =
chunks of
their exploration-phase land positions. </span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'text-align:justify;text-autospace:none'><span
style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;color:black'>And that&#146;s where Elgin comes =
in. With a
high-powered management team led by two of the more successful =
professionals in
the resource business &#151; Ian Rozier and Northern Orion&#146;s David =
Cohen &#151; the
company has already bought two platinum projects (Mareesburg and =
Rooikraal) in
South Africa this year, and is on the verge of buying a third =
(Spitzkop).</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'text-align:justify;text-autospace:none'><span
style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;color:black'>Mareesburg is a 2,129-hectare =
property
located on the Eastern Limb of South Africa&#146;s Bushveld Complex. =
Elgin took a 75.5% stake in this project&#146;s two-million =
ounce</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'text-align:justify;text-autospace:none'><span
style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;color:black'>platinum resource in February =
2004 with
the goal of bringing it into production within three years. Rooikrall, =
though more
speculative, is another Eastern Limb project with blue sky =
potential.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'text-align:justify;text-autospace:none'><span
style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;color:black'>But it is the deal for Spitzkop =
that has
garnered the market&#146;s attention of late. And rightfully so, as this =
property
hosts 10 million ounces of the five platinum group metals plus gold =
(5PGM+Au). This
inferred resource estimate is based on a 29,800-meter, 166-hole drilling
campaign conducted &#151; via a joint venture with Anglo Platinum &#151; =
by current owner
Impala Platinum.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'text-align:justify;text-autospace:none'><span
style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;color:black'>Located 12 kilometers north of =
and on the
same reef (UG2) as Mareesburg, the Spitzkop PGM project meets all of the
company&#146;s buying parameters. It&#146;s on the Eastern Limb. Its =
PGM-composition is
platinum-rich. And its near surface mineralization ensures rapid, =
low-cost
development.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'text-align:justify;text-autospace:none'><span
style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;color:black'>Of course, as you might expect, =
Elgin was not the only suitor for this choice piece of property. To =
improve its odds of being
the winning bidder, it decided to join forces with Jonpol Explorations, =
another
Canadian company.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'text-align:justify;text-autospace:none'><span
style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;color:black'>Because any new deals in South =
Africa have to include a Black Empowerment Enterprise (BEE) to receive =
regulatory approval,
the proposed purchase agreement is maddeningly Byzantine. But the upshot =
is as follows:</span></p>

